 299class ExecuteBatch(BaseRequests):
 300    """Executes a list of requests sequentially (one-by-one on the same thread).
 301
 302    Args:
 303        abortOnFail (bool): Stop processing batch requests if one returns a failure.
 304        requests (list): Array of requests to perform. Executed in order.
 305        requests.*.message-id (str): ID of the individual request. Can be any string and not required to be unique. Defaults to empty string if not specified.
 306        requests.*.request-type (str): Request type. Eg. `GetVersion`.
 307
 308    Returns:
 309        results (list): Batch requests results, ordered sequentially.
 310        results.*.error (str): Error message accompanying an `error` status.
 311        results.*.message-id (str): ID of the individual request which was originally provided by the client.
 312        results.*.status (str): Status response as string. Either `ok` or `error`.
 313    """
 314
 315    def __init__(self):
 316        """Init."""
 317
 318        super(ExecuteBatch, self).__init__()
 319
 320    async def init(
 321        self,
 322        abortOnFail: bool,
 323        requests: list,
 324        requests___message_id: str,
 325        requests___request_type: str,
 326    ):
 327        """Async init."""
 328
 329        self.name = 'ExecuteBatch'
 330        self.data_in['results'] = None
 331        self.data_in['results.*.error'] = None
 332        self.data_in['results.*.message-id'] = None
 333        self.data_in['results.*.status'] = None
 334        self.data_out['abortOnFail'] = abortOnFail
 335        self.data_out['requests'] = requests
 336        self.data_out['requests.*.message-id'] = requests___message_id
 337        self.data_out['requests.*.request-type'] = requests___request_type
 338        return self
 339
 340    async def get_results(self):
 341        return self.data_in['results']
 342
 343    async def get_results___error(self):
 344        return self.data_in['results.*.error']
 345
 346    async def get_results___message_id(self):
 347        return self.data_in['results.*.message-id']
 348
 349    async def get_results___status(self):
 350        return self.data_in['results.*.status']

1028
1029class GetSceneItemProperties(BaseRequests):
1030    """Gets the scene specific properties of the specified source item.
1031    Coordinates are relative to the item's parent (the scene or group it belongs to).
1032
1033        Args:
1034            item (str | object): Scene Item name (if this field is a string) or specification (if it is an object).
1035            item.id (int) optional: Scene Item ID (if the `item` field is an object)
1036            item.name (str) optional: Scene Item name (if the `item` field is an object)
1037            scene-name (str) optional: Name of the scene the scene item belongs to. Defaults to the current scene.
1038
1039        Returns:
1040            bounds.alignment (int): Alignment of the bounding box.
1041            bounds.type (str): Type of bounding box. Can be "OBS_BOUNDS_STRETCH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_INNER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_OUTER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_WIDTH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_HEIGHT", "OBS_BOUNDS_MAX_ONLY" or "OBS_BOUNDS_NONE".
1042            bounds.x (int): Width of the bounding box.
1043            bounds.y (int): Height of the bounding box.
1044            crop.bottom (int): The number of pixels cropped off the bottom of the source before scaling.
1045            crop.left (int): The number of pixels cropped off the left of the source before scaling.
1046            crop.right (int): The number of pixels cropped off the right of the source before scaling.
1047            crop.top (int): The number of pixels cropped off the top of the source before scaling.
1048            groupChildren (list): List of children (if this item is a group)
1049            height (int): Scene item height (base source height multiplied by the vertical scaling factor)
1050            itemId (int): Scene Item ID.
1051            locked (bool): If the source's transform is locked.
1052            muted (bool): If the source is muted.
1053            name (str): Scene Item name.
1054            parentGroupName (str): Name of the item's parent (if this item belongs to a group)
1055            position.alignment (int): The point on the source that the item is manipulated from. The sum of 1=Left or 2=Right, and 4=Top or 8=Bottom, or omit to center on that axis.
1056            position.x (int): The x position of the source from the left.
1057            position.y (int): The y position of the source from the top.
1058            rotation (int): The clockwise rotation of the item in degrees around the point of alignment.
1059            scale.filter (str): The scale filter of the source. Can be "OBS_SCALE_DISABLE", "OBS_SCALE_POINT", "OBS_SCALE_BICUBIC", "OBS_SCALE_BILINEAR", "OBS_SCALE_LANCZOS" or "OBS_SCALE_AREA".
1060            scale.x (int): The x-scale factor of the source.
1061            scale.y (int): The y-scale factor of the source.
1062            sourceHeight (int): Base source (without scaling) of the source
1063            sourceWidth (int): Base width (without scaling) of the source
1064            visible (bool): If the source is visible.
1065            width (int): Scene item width (base source width multiplied by the horizontal scaling factor)
1066    """
1067
1068    def __init__(self):
1069        """Init."""
1070

2457class OpenProjector(BaseRequests):
2458    """Open a projector window or create a projector on a monitor. Requires OBS v24.0.4 or newer.
2459
2460    Args:
2461        geometry (str): Size and position of the projector window (only if monitor is -1). Encoded in Base64 using [Qt's geometry encoding](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qwidget.html#saveGeometry). Corresponds to OBS's saved projectors.
2462        monitor (int): Monitor to open the projector on. If -1 or omitted, opens a window.
2463        name (str): Name of the source or scene to be displayed (ignored for other projector types).
2464        type (str): Type of projector: `Preview` (default), `Source`, `Scene`, `StudioProgram`, or `Multiview` (case insensitive).
2465    """
2466
2467    def __init__(self):
2468        """Init."""
2469
2470        super(OpenProjector, self).__init__()
2471
2472    async def init(self, geometry: str, monitor: int, name: str, type: str):
2473        """Async init."""
2474
2475        self.name = 'OpenProjector'
2476        self.data_out['geometry'] = geometry
2477        self.data_out['monitor'] = monitor
2478        self.data_out['name'] = name
2479        self.data_out['type'] = type
2480        return self
2481

3192class SetSceneItemProperties(BaseRequests):
3193    """Sets the scene specific properties of a source. Unspecified properties will remain unchanged.
3194    Coordinates are relative to the item's parent (the scene or group it belongs to).
3195
3196        Args:
3197            item (str | object): Scene Item name (if this field is a string) or specification (if it is an object).
3198            bounds.alignment (int) optional: The new alignment of the bounding box. (0-2, 4-6, 8-10)
3199            bounds.type (str) optional: The new bounds type of the source. Can be "OBS_BOUNDS_STRETCH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_INNER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_OUTER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_WIDTH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_HEIGHT", "OBS_BOUNDS_MAX_ONLY" or "OBS_BOUNDS_NONE".
3200            bounds.x (int) optional: The new width of the bounding box.
3201            bounds.y (int) optional: The new height of the bounding box.
3202            crop.bottom (int) optional: The new amount of pixels cropped off the bottom of the source before scaling.
3203            crop.left (int) optional: The new amount of pixels cropped off the left of the source before scaling.
3204            crop.right (int) optional: The new amount of pixels cropped off the right of the source before scaling.
3205            crop.top (int) optional: The new amount of pixels cropped off the top of the source before scaling.
3206            item.id (int) optional: Scene Item ID (if the `item` field is an object)
3207            item.name (str) optional: Scene Item name (if the `item` field is an object)
3208            locked (bool) optional: The new locked status of the source. 'true' keeps it in its current position, 'false' allows movement.
3209            position.alignment (int) optional: The new alignment of the source.
3210            position.x (int) optional: The new x position of the source.
3211            position.y (int) optional: The new y position of the source.
3212            rotation (int) optional: The new clockwise rotation of the item in degrees.
3213            scale.filter (str) optional: The new scale filter of the source. Can be "OBS_SCALE_DISABLE", "OBS_SCALE_POINT", "OBS_SCALE_BICUBIC", "OBS_SCALE_BILINEAR", "OBS_SCALE_LANCZOS" or "OBS_SCALE_AREA".
3214            scale.x (int) optional: The new x scale of the item.
3215            scale.y (int) optional: The new y scale of the item.
3216            scene-name (str) optional: Name of the scene the source item belongs to. Defaults to the current scene.
3217            visible (bool) optional: The new visibility of the source. 'true' shows source, 'false' hides source.
3218    """

3804    Args:
3805        source (str): Source name.
3806        volume (int): Desired volume. Must be between `0.0` and `20.0` for mul, and under 26.0 for dB. OBS will interpret dB values under -100.0 as Inf. Note: The OBS volume sliders only reach a maximum of 1.0mul/0.0dB, however OBS actually supports larger values.
3807        useDecibel (bool) optional: Interperet `volume` data as decibels instead of amplitude/mul.
3808    """
3809
3810    def __init__(self):
3811        """Init."""
3812
3813        super(SetVolume, self).__init__()
3814
3815    async def init(
3816        self, source: str, volume: int, useDecibel: Optional[bool] = None
3817    ):
3818        """Async init."""
3819
3820        self.name = 'SetVolume'
3821        self.data_out['source'] = source
3822        self.data_out['volume'] = volume
3823        self.data_out['useDecibel'] = useDecibel
3824        return self

3968        Args:

3970            stream.metadata (object) optional: Adds the given object parameters as encoded query string parameters to the 'key' of the RTMP stream. Used to pass data to the RTMP service about the streaming. May be any String, Numeric, or Boolean field.
3971            stream.settings (object) optional: Settings for the stream.
3972            stream.settings.key (str) optional: The publish key of the stream.
3973            stream.settings.password (str) optional: If authentication is enabled, the password for the streaming server. Ignored if `use_auth` is not set to `true`.
3974            stream.settings.server (str) optional: The publish URL.
3975            stream.settings.use_auth (bool) optional: Indicates whether authentication should be used when connecting to the streaming server.
3976            stream.settings.username (str) optional: If authentication is enabled, the username for the streaming server. Ignored if `use_auth` is not set to `true`.
3977            stream.type (str) optional: If specified ensures the type of stream matches the given type (usually 'rtmp_custom' or 'rtmp_common'). If the currently configured stream type does not match the given stream type, all settings must be specified in the `settings` object or an error will occur when starting the stream.

3994        stream_settings_username: Optional[str] = None,

3996    ):

4139class TakeSourceScreenshot(BaseRequests):
4140    """At least `embedPictureFormat` or `saveToFilePath` must be specified.
4141
4142    Clients can specify `width` and `height` parameters to receive scaled pictures. Aspect ratio is
4143    preserved if only one of these two parameters is specified.
4144
4145        Args:
4146            compressionQuality (int) optional: Compression ratio between -1 and 100 to write the image with. -1 is automatic, 1 is smallest file/most compression, 100 is largest file/least compression. Varies with image type.
4147            embedPictureFormat (str) optional: Format of the Data URI encoded picture. Can be "png", "jpg", "jpeg" or "bmp" (or any other value supported by Qt's Image module)
4148            fileFormat (str) optional: Format to save the image file as (one of the values provided in the `supported-image-export-formats` response field of `GetVersion`). If not specified, tries to guess based on file extension.
4149            height (int) optional: Screenshot height. Defaults to the source's base height.
4150            saveToFilePath (str) optional: Full file path (file extension included) where the captured image is to be saved. Can be in a format different from `pictureFormat`. Can be a relative path.
4151            sourceName (str) optional: Source name. Note: Since scenes are also sources, you can also provide a scene name. If not provided, the currently active scene is used.
4152            width (int) optional: Screenshot width. Defaults to the source's base width.
4153
4154        Returns:
4155            imageFile (str): Absolute path to the saved image file (if `saveToFilePath` was specified in the request)
4156            img (str): Image Data URI (if `embedPictureFormat` was specified in the request)
4157            sourceName (str): Source name
4158    """
4159
4160    def __init__(self):
4161        """Init."""
4162
4163        super(TakeSourceScreenshot, self).__init__()
4164
4165    async def init(
4166        self,
4167        compressionQuality: Optional[int] = None,
4168        embedPictureFormat: Optional[str] = None,
4169        fileFormat: Optional[str] = None,
4170        height: Optional[int] = None,
4171        saveToFilePath: Optional[str] = None,
4172        sourceName: Optional[str] = None,
4173        width: Optional[int] = None,
4174    ):
4175        """Async init."""
4176
4177        self.name = 'TakeSourceScreenshot'
4178        self.data_in['imageFile'] = None
4179        self.data_in['img'] = None
4180        self.data_in['sourceName'] = None
4181        self.data_out['compressionQuality'] = compressionQuality
4182        self.data_out['embedPictureFormat'] = embedPictureFormat
4183        self.data_out['fileFormat'] = fileFormat
4184        self.data_out['height'] = height
4185        self.data_out['saveToFilePath'] = saveToFilePath
4186        self.data_out['sourceName'] = sourceName
4187        self.data_out['width'] = width
4188        return self

class ExecuteBatch(obs.obs_base_classes.BaseRequests): 
300class ExecuteBatch(BaseRequests):
301    """Executes a list of requests sequentially (one-by-one on the same thread).
302
303    Args:
304        abortOnFail (bool): Stop processing batch requests if one returns a failure.
305        requests (list): Array of requests to perform. Executed in order.
306        requests.*.message-id (str): ID of the individual request. Can be any string and not required to be unique. Defaults to empty string if not specified.
307        requests.*.request-type (str): Request type. Eg. `GetVersion`.
308
309    Returns:
310        results (list): Batch requests results, ordered sequentially.
311        results.*.error (str): Error message accompanying an `error` status.
312        results.*.message-id (str): ID of the individual request which was originally provided by the client.
313        results.*.status (str): Status response as string. Either `ok` or `error`.
314    """
315
316    def __init__(self):
317        """Init."""
318
319        super(ExecuteBatch, self).__init__()
320
321    async def init(
322        self,
323        abortOnFail: bool,
324        requests: list,
325        requests___message_id: str,
326        requests___request_type: str,
327    ):
328        """Async init."""
329
330        self.name = 'ExecuteBatch'
331        self.data_in['results'] = None
332        self.data_in['results.*.error'] = None
333        self.data_in['results.*.message-id'] = None
334        self.data_in['results.*.status'] = None
335        self.data_out['abortOnFail'] = abortOnFail
336        self.data_out['requests'] = requests
337        self.data_out['requests.*.message-id'] = requests___message_id
338        self.data_out['requests.*.request-type'] = requests___request_type
339        return self
340
341    async def get_results(self):
342        return self.data_in['results']
343
344    async def get_results___error(self):
345        return self.data_in['results.*.error']
346
347    async def get_results___message_id(self):
348        return self.data_in['results.*.message-id']
349
350    async def get_results___status(self):
351        return self.data_in['results.*.status']

Executed in order. requests..message-id (str): ID of the individual request. Can be any string and not required to be unique. Defaults to empty string if not specified. requests..request-type (str): Request type. Eg. GetVersion.

class GetSceneItemProperties(obs.obs_base_classes.BaseRequests): 
1030class GetSceneItemProperties(BaseRequests):
1031    """Gets the scene specific properties of the specified source item.
1032    Coordinates are relative to the item's parent (the scene or group it belongs to).
1033
1034        Args:
1035            item (str | object): Scene Item name (if this field is a string) or specification (if it is an object).
1036            item.id (int) optional: Scene Item ID (if the `item` field is an object)
1037            item.name (str) optional: Scene Item name (if the `item` field is an object)
1038            scene-name (str) optional: Name of the scene the scene item belongs to. Defaults to the current scene.
1039
1040        Returns:
1041            bounds.alignment (int): Alignment of the bounding box.
1042            bounds.type (str): Type of bounding box. Can be "OBS_BOUNDS_STRETCH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_INNER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_OUTER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_WIDTH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_HEIGHT", "OBS_BOUNDS_MAX_ONLY" or "OBS_BOUNDS_NONE".
1043            bounds.x (int): Width of the bounding box.
1044            bounds.y (int): Height of the bounding box.
1045            crop.bottom (int): The number of pixels cropped off the bottom of the source before scaling.
1046            crop.left (int): The number of pixels cropped off the left of the source before scaling.
1047            crop.right (int): The number of pixels cropped off the right of the source before scaling.
1048            crop.top (int): The number of pixels cropped off the top of the source before scaling.
1049            groupChildren (list): List of children (if this item is a group)
1050            height (int): Scene item height (base source height multiplied by the vertical scaling factor)
1051            itemId (int): Scene Item ID.
1052            locked (bool): If the source's transform is locked.
1053            muted (bool): If the source is muted.
1054            name (str): Scene Item name.
1055            parentGroupName (str): Name of the item's parent (if this item belongs to a group)
1056            position.alignment (int): The point on the source that the item is manipulated from. The sum of 1=Left or 2=Right, and 4=Top or 8=Bottom, or omit to center on that axis.
1057            position.x (int): The x position of the source from the left.
1058            position.y (int): The y position of the source from the top.
1059            rotation (int): The clockwise rotation of the item in degrees around the point of alignment.
1060            scale.filter (str): The scale filter of the source. Can be "OBS_SCALE_DISABLE", "OBS_SCALE_POINT", "OBS_SCALE_BICUBIC", "OBS_SCALE_BILINEAR", "OBS_SCALE_LANCZOS" or "OBS_SCALE_AREA".
1061            scale.x (int): The x-scale factor of the source.
1062            scale.y (int): The y-scale factor of the source.
1063            sourceHeight (int): Base source (without scaling) of the source
1064            sourceWidth (int): Base width (without scaling) of the source
1065            visible (bool): If the source is visible.
1066            width (int): Scene item width (base source width multiplied by the horizontal scaling factor)
1067    """

Gets the scene specific properties of the specified source item. Coordinates are relative to the item's parent (the scene or group it belongs to).

Args:
    item (str | object): Scene Item name (if this field is a string) or specification (if it is an object).
    item.id (int) optional: Scene Item ID (if the `item` field is an object)
    item.name (str) optional: Scene Item name (if the `item` field is an object)
    scene-name (str) optional: Name of the scene the scene item belongs to. Defaults to the current scene.

Returns:
    bounds.alignment (int): Alignment of the bounding box.
    bounds.type (str): Type of bounding box. Can be "OBS_BOUNDS_STRETCH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_INNER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_OUTER", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_WIDTH", "OBS_BOUNDS_SCALE_TO_HEIGHT", "OBS_BOUNDS_MAX_ONLY" or "OBS_BOUNDS_NONE".
    bounds.x (int): Width of the bounding box.
    bounds.y (int): Height of the bounding box.
    crop.bottom (int): The number of pixels cropped off the bottom of the source before scaling.
    crop.left (int): The number of pixels cropped off the left of the source before scaling.
    crop.right (int): The number of pixels cropped off the right of the source before scaling.
    crop.top (int): The number of pixels cropped off the top of the source before scaling.
    groupChildren (list): List of children (if this item is a group)
    height (int): Scene item height (base source height multiplied by the vertical scaling factor)
    itemId (int): Scene Item ID.
    locked (bool): If the source's transform is locked.
    muted (bool): If the source is muted.
    name (str): Scene Item name.
    parentGroupName (str): Name of the item's parent (if this item belongs to a group)
    position.alignment (int): The point on the source that the item is manipulated from. The sum of 1=Left or 2=Right, and 4=Top or 8=Bottom, or omit to center on that axis.
    position.x (int): The x position of the source from the left.
    position.y (int): The y position of the source from the top.
    rotation (int): The clockwise rotation of the item in degrees around the point of alignment.
    scale.filter (str): The scale filter of the source. Can be "OBS_SCALE_DISABLE", "OBS_SCALE_POINT", "OBS_SCALE_BICUBIC", "OBS_SCALE_BILINEAR", "OBS_SCALE_LANCZOS" or "OBS_SCALE_AREA".
    scale.x (int): The x-scale factor of the source.
    scale.y (int): The y-scale factor of the source.
    sourceHeight (int): Base source (without scaling) of the source
    sourceWidth (int): Base width (without scaling) of the source
    visible (bool): If the source is visible.

4140class TakeSourceScreenshot(BaseRequests):
4141    """At least `embedPictureFormat` or `saveToFilePath` must be specified.
4142
4143    Clients can specify `width` and `height` parameters to receive scaled pictures. Aspect ratio is
4144    preserved if only one of these two parameters is specified.
4145
4146        Args:
4147            compressionQuality (int) optional: Compression ratio between -1 and 100 to write the image with. -1 is automatic, 1 is smallest file/most compression, 100 is largest file/least compression. Varies with image type.
4148            embedPictureFormat (str) optional: Format of the Data URI encoded picture. Can be "png", "jpg", "jpeg" or "bmp" (or any other value supported by Qt's Image module)
4149            fileFormat (str) optional: Format to save the image file as (one of the values provided in the `supported-image-export-formats` response field of `GetVersion`). If not specified, tries to guess based on file extension.
4150            height (int) optional: Screenshot height. Defaults to the source's base height.
4151            saveToFilePath (str) optional: Full file path (file extension included) where the captured image is to be saved. Can be in a format different from `pictureFormat`. Can be a relative path.
4152            sourceName (str) optional: Source name. Note: Since scenes are also sources, you can also provide a scene name. If not provided, the currently active scene is used.
4153            width (int) optional: Screenshot width. Defaults to the source's base width.
4154
4155        Returns:
4156            imageFile (str): Absolute path to the saved image file (if `saveToFilePath` was specified in the request)

At least embedPictureFormat or saveToFilePath must be specified.

Clients can specify width and height parameters to receive scaled pictures. Aspect ratio is preserved if only one of these two parameters is specified.

Args:
    compressionQuality (int) optional: Compression ratio between -1 and 100 to write the image with. -1 is automatic, 1 is smallest file/most compression, 100 is largest file/least compression. Varies with image type.
    embedPictureFormat (str) optional: Format of the Data URI encoded picture. Can be "png", "jpg", "jpeg" or "bmp" (or any other value supported by Qt's Image module)
    fileFormat (str) optional: Format to save the image file as (one of the values provided in the `supported-image-export-formats` response field of `GetVersion`). If not specified, tries to guess based on file extension.
    height (int) optional: Screenshot height. Defaults to the source's base height.
    saveToFilePath (str) optional: Full file path (file extension included) where the captured image is to be saved. Can be in a format different from `pictureFormat`. Can be a relative path.
    sourceName (str) optional: Source name. Note: Since scenes are also sources, you can also provide a scene name. If not provided, the currently active scene is used.
    width (int) optional: Screenshot width. Defaults to the source's base width.

Returns:
    imageFile (str): Absolute path to the saved image file (if `saveToFilePath` was specified in the request)
    img (str): Image Data URI (if `embedPictureFormat` was specified in the request)
    sourceName (str): Source name
